OL,3,C'Explosions were going off' - Battery
OL,4,Cwarning after bin lorry fires
OL,6,FWhy is it dangerous to throw lithium
OL,7,Fbatteries in the bin?
OL,9,FLithium batteries, which are used in
OL,10,Fvapes as well as other products, can
OL,11,Fgenerate large amounts of gas which
OL,12,Fcan pose a fire risk.
OL,14,FProf Paul Christensen, from Newcastle
OL,15,FUniversity, said: "They generate very
OL,16,Flarge quantities of gas when they're
OL,17,Fabused, classic example is being
OL,18,Fcrushed for example in a bin lorry.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/8
